.TH "pci_bus_find_capability" 9 "pci_bus_find_capability" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_bus_find_capability \- query for devices' capabilities
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u8" pci_bus_find_capability
.BI "(struct pci_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "unsigned int devfn "  ","
.BI "int cap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
the PCI bus to query
.IP "devfn" 12
PCI device to query
.IP "cap" 12
capability code
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Like \fBpci_find_capability\fP but works for PCI devices that do not have a
pci_dev structure set up yet.

Returns the address of the requested capability structure within the
device's PCI configuration space or 0 in case the device does not
support it.
